    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Medicare Law: Some Call It Betrayal</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jean Garfinkle letter cannot believe that Congress and AARP concocted 'disgraceful' Medicare drug legislation</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Having read ''New Medicare Plan for Drug Benefits Prohibits Insurance'' (front page, Dec. 7), about just one provision of the Medicare law, I cannot believe that Congress and the AARP concocted this disgraceful legislation. I dread hearing about the rest of the provisions.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Having read ''New Medicare Plan for Drug Benefits Prohibits Insurance'' (front page, Dec. 7), about just one provision of the Medicare law, I cannot believe that Congress and the AARP concocted this disgraceful legislation. I dread hearing about the rest of the provisions.</p>
        <p>The people who formed the backbone of this country have been betrayed. They deserve true representation. I hope that an organization that functions in a democratic manner will emerge soon.</p>
        <p>JEAN GARFINKLE  Bronx, Dec. 7, 2003</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
